@Data
@AllArgsConstructor
@NoArgsConstructor
public class Person {
    private String name;
    private int age;
}


Or immutable version:

@Value
public class Person {
    String name;
    int age;
}


What Lombok does-
Generates boilerplate at compile time
Requires Lombok dependency + IDE plugin
Works on any Java version (8+)

When to use Lombok?
    Best use cases
        JPA entities (@Entity)
        Mutable domain models
        Legacy Java 8 projects
        Classes needing setters
        Inheritance-based designs

Examle JPA Entity-
 @Entity
 @Data
 @NoArgsConstructor
 @AllArgsConstructor
 public class User {
     @Id
     private Long id;
     private String email;
 }


⚠️ Important
    JPA + records ❌ (not officially supported / tricky)
    Lombok works very well with JPA


Real-world recommendation (very important)
    Modern Java backend projects:
        Records → DTOs, API models, Kafka messages
        Lombok → Entities, domain models, mutable objects
